:3,"total":3,"comments":[{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12601076/comment/13426690","id":"13426690","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=gnt","name":"gnt","emailAddress":"gnodet at apache dot org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Guillaume Nodet","active":true},"body":"Unfortunately, the spec says that service reference should fetch the service lazily.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=gnt","name":"gnt","emailAddress":"gnodet at apache dot org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Guillaume Nodet","active":true},"created":"2012-08-01T15:16:17.652+0000","updated":"2012-08-01T15:16:17.652+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12601076/comment/13426730","id":"13426730","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=gnt","name":"gnt","emailAddress":"gnodet at apache dot org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Guillaume Nodet","active":true},"body":"Actually, the problem is different. The bad usage comes from the fact that the ReferenceRecipe#bind() is called twice.\r\nOnce when the manager is started, and once when the recipe is created to make sure listeners are called.\r\nThis second call cause the ungetService() method to be called and lower the usage of the service.\r\nThe service should only be unget if the new tracked ServiceReference is different from the old one.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=gnt","name":"gnt","emailAddress":"gnodet at apache dot org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Guillaume Nodet","active":true},"created":"2012-08-01T16:19:23.434+0000","updated":"2012-08-01T16:19:23.434+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12601076/comment/13426839","id":"13426839","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=gnt","name":"gnt","emailAddress":"gnodet at apache dot org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Guillaume Nodet","active":true},"body":"http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?rev=1368208&view=rev","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=gnt","name":"gnt","emailAddress":"gnodet at apache dot org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/s